HEADWORD: Zooecium
<hw>Zo*oe"ci*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Zooecia</plw> <pr>(?)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>zw^,on</grk> an animal + <?/ house.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the cells or tubes which inclose the feeling zooids of
Bryozoa. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Sea Moss</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

